# Docker Hub & the alternatives

**Docker Hub** (`docker.io`) is the default — `docker pull nginx` hits it. Free public, but **rate-limited** anonymous pulls (~100 / IP / 6h) — the top reason to run a cache.

## The ones you'll meet

| Registry | Host | For |
|---|---|---|
| **GHCR** | `ghcr.io` | GitHub / OSS — Actions-integrated |
| **AWS ECR** | `…dkr.ecr…` | AWS, IAM auth |
| **Google AR** | `…pkg.dev` | GCP |
| **Azure ACR** | `…azurecr.io` | Azure |
| **Harbor** | self-host | on-prem: RBAC, scan, replicate |
| **`registry:2`** | self-host | OSS server; testing, air-gapped |

## They all speak OCI

Mix freely — build in CI, push to GHCR, mirror to ECR, cache locally. **Same `push`/`pull`; only the hostname changes.** Choice = where workloads run + self-host or not.
